# vfox SDK manifest — synced across machines via dotfiles.
#
# Format: one entry per line, `plugin@version`. Comments start with #.
# Use `@latest` (vfox-supported alias) to always pull the newest stable
# release on each `dotfiles install`. Pin a concrete version (e.g.
# `nodejs@24.15.0`) when you need reproducibility.
#
# Note: `@lts` is NOT a vfox alias — plugins handle it inconsistently.
# Use a concrete version if you want the latest LTS specifically.
#
# Official plugins (version-fox/*):   nodejs, golang, python
# Community plugins (third-party):    bun
#
# Rust intentionally omitted — use rustup directly (canonical Rust toolchain).
#
# To apply changes: edit, then run `dotfiles install` (re-runs pkg_post_install).

nodejs@latest
golang@latest
python@latest
bun@latest
